============================================================
PHASE 8 OBJECTIVE
============================================================

Build the production-hardening layer for zDash.

Main goals:

1. Add persistent database storage
2. Add SQLAlchemy models and migrations
3. Add Auth system with JWT
4. Add RBAC roles and permissions
5. Add protected backend APIs
6. Add frontend login/session handling
7. Add audit log persistence
8. Add production-grade Docker setup
9. Add Redis-ready service wiring
10. Add NGINX reverse proxy config
11. Add Prometheus-compatible metrics endpoint
12. Add structured observability
13. Add backup and restore scripts
14. Add CI test/build workflow
15. Add production safety gates
16. Keep DRY_RUN and approval-required safety defaults

IMPORTANT:
- Do not enable live trading by default.
- Do not enable real IoT actions by default.
- Do not enable real social posting by default.
- Do not expose secrets in frontend or logs.
- Do not weaken Guardian risk controls.
- Do not bypass approval gates.
- All production features must fail safely.
- This phase hardens the system; it must not make dangerous automation easier.

