Do not require Alembic unless you also generate full Alembic configuration cleanly.

============================================================
AUTH REQUIREMENTS
============================================================

Create JWT auth system.

Required endpoints:

POST /api/auth/login

Request:

{
  "email": "admin@zdash.local",
  "password": "password"
}

Response:
- access_token
- refresh_token
- token_type
- expires_in
- user

POST /api/auth/refresh

Request:
{
  "refresh_token": "..."
}

Response:
- new access_token
- refresh_token rotation result

POST /api/auth/logout

Behavior:
- invalidates refresh token

GET /api/auth/me

Returns:
- current user
- roles
- permissions

POST /api/auth/bootstrap-admin

Behavior:
- creates default admin only if no users exist
- disabled in production unless explicitly allowed

User fields:

- id
- email
- display_name
- role
- is_active
- created_at
- updated_at

Roles:

- admin
- operator
- analyst
- viewer

Permissions:

admin:
- all permissions

operator:
- read dashboard
- run dry-run trading
- manage scheduler
- manage content approval
- run backtests
- control dry-run IoT
- halt/resume risk system

analyst:
- read dashboard
- run backtests
- read logs
- read risk
- read trading signals

viewer:
- read dashboard only

Sensitive actions requiring admin or operator:
- risk halt
- risk resume
- scheduler job create/update/delete
- IoT power actions
- content approval
- content publish dry-run
- backtest promotion check

Admin-only:
- user management
- metrics when METRICS_AUTH_REQUIRED=true
- production safety config
- audit log export

